<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title> Week 4 
        Responsive Layout</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="week4 style.css">
</head>
<body>

    <div class="page-container">
        <!-- Header Section -->
        <header class="page-header">
            <h1>My Responsive Website</h1>
        </header>
        <nav class="main-nav">
            <ul>
                <li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
                <li><a href="#">About</a></li>
                <li><a href="#">Services</a></li>
                <li><a href="#">Contact</a></li>
            </ul>
        </nav>

        <!-- Main Content & Sidebar -->
        <main class="main-content">
            <section class="content-area">
                <h2>Content Section (Grid)</h2>
                <p>This section is part of the main grid layout. On a desktop, it sits next to the sidebar. On a tablet, it moves above the sidebar. On a mobile phone, it takes up the full width of the screen.</p>
                
                <div class="card-container">
                    <div class="card">
                        <h3>Flex Card 1</h3>
                        <p>This card and its siblings are laid out using Flexbox for easy alignment.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card">
                        <h3>Flex Card 2</h3>
                        <p>Flexbox is ideal for arranging a series of items in a single row or column, like these cards.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card">
                        <h3>Flex Card 3</h3>
                        <p>As the screen shrinks, the cards will wrap to the next line to maintain a clean layout.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
        </main>

        <aside class="sidebar">
            <h3>Sidebar (Grid)</h3>
            <p>This sidebar is an integral part of the main grid. On desktop, it sits to the side. On mobile and tablet, it adapts to the new layout using media queries.</p>
        </aside>

        <!-- Footer Section -->
        <footer class="page-footer">
            <p>&copy; 2024 Responsive Layout. All rights reserved.</p>
        </footer>
    </div>

</body>
</html>
